states have
caucuses, and some states have
actual conventions

19:07.380 --> 19:12.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
where delegates are voted on.
These are things
that have been set in place
since October

19:12.151 --> 19:16.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of 2015. All the candidates have
been briefed.
They have all been aware of the
rules. They're

19:16.722 --> 19:18.824 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
out there for the whole world to
see.

19:18.924 --> 19:24.397 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is nothing mysterious
about it. And,
by the way, no one complained
either before

19:24.497 --> 19:29.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
