20:52.718 --> 20:59.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have to be some kind of an
expert to understand
all this. Is it really
democratic anymore?

20:59.358 --> 21:01.127 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I mean with a small D.

21:01.227 --> 21:04.396 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
REINCE PRIEBUS: Of course it is.

21:04.497 --> 21:10.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the same method that we
have been using,
and the Democrats use the same
delegate method.

21:10.436 --> 21:17.143 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're not a public entity. We're
an organization
that is made up of members
across this country

21:17.243 --> 21:22.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and state parties. State parties
have a right
to determine how each of their
delegates get

21:22.948 --> 21:25.050 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to go to the national
convention.

21:25.151 --> 21:30.055 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You know, 150 years ago,
delegates ran in
the states, and they just went
to the convention

21:30.156 --> 21:34.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
