40:50.915 --> 40:54.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The Danish
politician, former
center-left Interior Minister
Morten Ostergaard,

40:54.886 --> 41:00.425 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
is concerned that
asylum-seekers' rights under
international law are possibly
being breached,

41:00.525 --> 41:03.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but doubts whether Pope Francis
is the catalyst
for change.

41:03.494 --> 41:05.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MORTEN OSTERGAARD, Former Danish
Interior
Minister: At least what I think
that the pope

41:05.897 --> 41:12.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can do is perhaps shed a bit of
hope in the
people who are desperate. But,
politically,

41:12.570 --> 41:16.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's up to people like me and
the political
leaders in the European Union to
make a difference.

41:16.574 --> 41:18.609 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We can't let -- leave that to
the pope.

41:18.710 --> 41:23.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: And this is
Spyros Galinos,
the mayor of Lesbos, who was
instrumental

41:23.915 --> 41:28.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in inviting the pope to draw
attention to
the plight of the refugees and
the islanders'

41:28.486 --> 41:30.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
burden.

41:30.355 --> 41:32.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SPYROS GALINOS, Mayor of Lesbos,
Greece: It
is a visit of enormous symbolic
importance.

41:32.990 --> 41:36.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we hope that all governments
will follow
the pope's lead and finally move
in the right

41:37.095 --> 41:39.163 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
direction for all the peoples of
Europe.

41:39.263 --> 41:44.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: On a religious
level, the
pope's visit is fraught with
difficulties.

41:44.802 --> 41:51.876 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Catholic and Orthodox
churches split cataclysmically
1,000 years ago, and are still
unable to resolve

41:51.976 --> 41:53.878 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
differences.

41:53.978 --> 41:58.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are some forces within
orthodoxy that
are seeking reconciliation, but
leading theologian

41:58.549 --> 42:01.219 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Panayotis Tsagaris is skeptical.

42:01.319 --> 42:08.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PANAYOTIS TSAGARIS, Theologian
(through translator):
We consider that the pope's
visit is little

42:08.693 --> 42:13.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
more than a public relations
exercise which
will not provide any real
solution to the

42:13.164 --> 42:18.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
refugee problem facing not only
my island
and country, but also extending
to Europe.

42:18.703 --> 42:23.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The fraught
history between
the two churches has even led
some ultra-conservative

42:23.775 --> 42:28.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
religious leaders to call the
papal mission
a stab in the back. One
archbishop expressed

42:28.746 --> 42:33.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
concern that hiding among the
migrants are
Islamic extremists on a mission
to undermine

42:34.018 --> 42:36.421 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Europe and its traditions.

42:36.521 --> 42:42.660 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But on the waterfront in
Greece's main port,
Piraeus, their Orthodox Church
is demonstrating

42:42.760 --> 42:51.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
its willingness to reach across
the religious
divide. Every day, the church's
charity, Apostoli,

42:51.502 --> 42:55.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
distributes 1,000 meals to
asylum-seekers
living rough on the harbor.

42:55.339 --> 43:00.211 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Spokeswoman Despina Katsivelaki
rejects the
Islamophobic wing of orthodoxy.

43:00.311 --> 43:05.450 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DESPINA KATSIVELAKI, Apostoli
(through translator):
We help human beings, regardless
of their

43:05.550 --> 43:11.222 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
race, religion, color,
nationality. That's
what we do. That's our role and
aim, and that's

43:11.322 --> 43:13.758 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what we try to succeed in doing.

43:13.858 --> 43:18.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Although the
islanders are
desperate for the human tide to
diminish,

43:19.030 --> 43:23.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there's profound empathy for
people escaping
conflict and trying to improve
themselves,

43:23.935 --> 43:27.505 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because Greeks have a similar
history.

43:27.605 --> 43:31.809 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Father Athanasios Giousmas is
the chief priest
at the Exquisite Church in
Mytilini, Lesbos'

43:31.909 --> 43:33.678 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
main town.

43:33.778 --> 43:35.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FATHER ATHANASIOS GIOUSMAS,
Exquisite Church
(through translator): This is
why we have

43:35.980 --> 43:41.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
such mixed feelings within
ourselves, not
only pain for these refugees,
but also agony

43:41.752 --> 43:46.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about what is likely to happen
generally,
and in this country, together
with disgust

43:46.424 --> 43:51.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- and forgive me for saying so
-- but disgust,
not only for the world leaders,
but also those

43:51.796 --> 43:53.564 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
here in Greece.

43:53.664 --> 43:59.770 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Despite
misgivings about
the E.U.-Turkey accord, it seems
to be working

43:59.871 --> 44:05.710 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as its deal-makers intended. The
numbers of
arrivals are substantially down.

44:05.810 --> 44:10.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Spanish lifeguards have returned
from patrols
empty-handed for nearly two
weeks. The Turks

44:10.781 --> 44:14.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are either upholding their end
of the bargain,
or the boats are being
intercepted by the

44:14.919 --> 44:16.787 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
E.U. border agency.

44:16.888 --> 44:21.993 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The big question is, will the
despair on Lesbos
filter back down the migrant
trail and deter

44:22.093 --> 44:26.464 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the throng, or will they find
new routes to
reach their goal?

44:26.564 --> 44:29.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant
in Lesbos.

44:29.700 --> 44:35.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And there will be
more on the
pope's visit to Lesbos on "PBS
NewsHour Weekend,"

44:35.606 --> 44:41.412 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
right here on most of these PBS
stations.

44:41.512 --> 44:57.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Next: music with a purpose, a
story about
a violinist charting her own
musical path.

44:57.862 --> 45:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown tells us exactly
how her music
is hitting the spirit.

45:02.633 --> 45:09.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: It was an
unlikely setting
for a classical music
performance: a homeless

45:09.540 --> 45:18.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
shelter, the Community for
Creative Non-Violence,
in the shadow of the nation's
capital, where

45:18.549 --> 45:28.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
concert violinist Rachel Barton
Pine played
a special engagement for the
residents.

45:28.326 --> 45:38.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was music from many eras
and styles.
Along the way, Pine offered bits
of musical

45:38.803 --> 45:40.438 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
history.

45:40.538 --> 45:42.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE, Violinist:
So, Mozart
was from Germany from the late
1700s.

45:42.239 --> 45:44.342 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And told them a
bit about herself.

45:44.442 --> 45:48.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: And we were
often one
missed payment away from losing
the roof over

45:48.579 --> 45:51.415 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
our heads, which was the
scariest thing of
all when I was a little kid.

45:51.515 --> 45:55.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Pine, in fact,
knows something
of the plight of her audience.
Her father

45:56.053 --> 45:59.123 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was mostly unemployed, and the
family had
to scrape by.

45:59.223 --> 46:05.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: So, We had
these three
sort of grocery crates rescued
from the garbage

46:05.429 --> 46:09.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and this one little electric
heater. And I
would rotate it every 10
minutes, so that,

46:09.567 --> 46:13.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as part of me was warming up and
thawing,
another part would be starting
to freeze.

46:13.704 --> 46:19.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we had to do unusual things,
like get
my concert clothes from a thrift
store and

46:19.810 --> 46:23.581 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
try to fix them up to be
something presentable
for stage.

46:23.681 --> 46:27.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: These days, Pine
tours the
world a good part of the year,
traveling with

46:27.952 --> 46:33.024 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her husband, Greg, who serves as
her manager,
and their 4-year-old daughter.

46:33.124 --> 46:35.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But she feels a pull to give
back wherever
she goes.

46:36.093 --> 46:40.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: Sometimes, I
go to hospitals.
I have even been to prisons, and
just wherever

46:40.831 --> 46:44.635 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
music can uplift people's
spirits. That's
the meaning of being a musician.

46:44.735 --> 46:48.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But you have a
life on the
road that is different, in the
sort of traditional

46:48.339 --> 46:50.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
performing and then playing in
places like
this.

46:51.075 --> 46:52.777 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: Absolutely.

46:52.877 --> 46:56.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, yes, I think more and more
artists,
especially with the younger
generation, are

46:56.614 --> 47:02.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
really understanding the value
of community
engagement. If we only played
for the converted,

47:03.054 --> 47:06.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we would be not honoring our
gifts to the
fullest extent.

47:06.557 --> 47:12.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: One spirit lifted
today, Ray
Simmons, who told us of falling
on hard times

47:12.730 --> 47:15.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and finding hope in Pine's music
and his own.

47:15.900 --> 47:18.035 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Do you have to hold onto
something?

47:18.135 --> 47:19.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAY SIMMONS, The Community for
Creative Non-Violence:
You have to hold onto something.
You have

47:19.403 --> 47:20.604 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to hold onto your sanity.

47:20.705 --> 47:21.205 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

47:21.305 --> 47:21.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

47:21.839 --> 47:23.240 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
RAY SIMMONS: Yes.

47:23.340 --> 47:25.142 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For you, it
sounds like you
hold onto your music too.

47:25.242 --> 47:27.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAY SIMMONS: I hold onto my
music quite often.
That's what gets me through,
knowing that

47:27.578 --> 47:30.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm going to -- yes, I'm going
to play my
way out and sing my way out of
this place,

47:30.648 --> 47:32.616 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for sure, for sure.

47:32.717 --> 47:41.525 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Pine started
young. She gave
her first recital at age 5,
played with a

47:41.625 --> 47:45.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
professional orchestra at 7, and
with one
of the great ones, the Chicago
Symphony, in

47:45.229 --> 47:47.698 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a concert of young performers at
age 10.

47:47.798 --> 47:54.505 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: And now super-duper Rachel
Barton makes
her debut with the Chicago
Symphony Orchestra.

47:54.605 --> 47:56.874 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

47:56.974 --> 48:08.419 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: In recent years,
she formed
a foundation to help what she
calls poor prodigies

48:08.519 --> 48:15.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with things not covered by
traditional scholarships:
accompaniment fees, sheet music,
transportation

48:15.126 --> 48:17.027 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to competitions.

48:17.128 --> 48:23.734 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To date, she's helped 70 young
people. Another
project, Global HeartStrings,
supports aspiring

48:23.834 --> 48:26.270 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
musicians in developing
countries such as
Haiti.

48:26.370 --> 48:30.341 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: Music
programs here in
America, we kind of take for
granted, like

48:30.441 --> 48:37.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
rosin to put on your bow hair,
or, you know,
a shoulder rest, so that your
violin will

48:37.481 --> 48:39.283 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sit on your body properly.

48:39.383 --> 48:44.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: At 21, on the
brink of a major
career, the doors of a Chicago
commuter train

48:44.655 --> 48:51.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
closed on the straps of her
violin case, trapping
Pine. The train dragged her 200
feet, severing

48:51.896 --> 48:57.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her left leg and mangling her
right foot.
Fifty surgeries later, she walks
on a prosthetic

48:57.701 --> 48:59.470 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
leg.

48:59.570 --> 49:01.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: Really, of
course, it
was a case of corporate
negligence, because

49:01.806 --> 49:07.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there had been many, many prior
instances
before the day that I happened
to get hurt.

49:07.111 --> 49:10.748 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, thankfully, they have
changed their safety
procedures. Everybody has
something they have

49:10.848 --> 49:13.918 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to deal with, and this just
happens to be
mine.

49:14.018 --> 49:19.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And the concert
violinist is
also a heavy metal lover and
performer, a

49:19.723 --> 49:23.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
regular headbanger, here playing
Metallica's
"One."

49:23.327 --> 49:30.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: So, at
first, it was like
the mainstream bands, but then I
started to

49:30.568 --> 49:38.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get into the classic thrash
groups like Anthrax,
Megadeth, Slayer, early
Metallica, Pantera

49:38.509 --> 49:42.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
(INAUDIBLE). Like, this music
just grabbed
me. It was so intense.

49:43.047 --> 49:46.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But you were
playing classical
music, playing Bach during the
day, and then

49:46.784 --> 49:47.618 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
at 10:00, you're listening to...

49:47.718 --> 49:48.352 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: Anthrax.

49:48.452 --> 49:50.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Anthrax.

49:50.354 --> 49:52.923 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: So, it
sounds silly to
say I relaxed to this like
headbanging metal,

49:53.023 --> 49:56.827 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but, yes, I could just turn off
my brain and
rock out.

49:56.927 --> 49:59.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I started playing these things
on my instrument
and realized, wait a sec, this
is actually

50:00.097 --> 50:01.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
very sophisticated music.

50:01.498 --> 50:05.603 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For us, she
played Ozzy Osbourne's
"Crazy Train."

50:05.703 --> 50:15.246 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Maybe, Pine says, she can help
bridge these
disparate musical worlds.

50:15.346 --> 50:22.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RACHEL BARTON PINE: One of my
goals has to
been to get fellow headbangers
out to the

50:22.152 --> 50:27.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
symphony. There is nothing more
intense than
100 people on stage playing the
Tchaikovsky

50:27.191 --> 50:33.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Violin Concerto. And, you know,
it's just
an experience like none other.

50:33.330 --> 50:44.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A hundred people
on stage,
or one at a homeless shelter,
where Rachel

50:44.475 --> 50:51.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Barton Pine gave residents a
taste of her
newly released album, her 30th,
called "Testament:

50:51.415 --> 50:55.319 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Bach's Sonatas and Partitas for
Solo Violin."

